name: Oddish
flavorText: If exposed to moonlight, it starts to move. It roams far and wide at night to scatter its seeds.

name: Gloom
flavorText: Its pistils exude an incredibly foul odor. The horrid stench can cause fainting at a distance of 1.25 miles.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Vileplume
flavorText: It has the world's largest petals. With every step, the petals shake out heavy clouds of toxic pollen.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, they can't play any Supporter cards from their hand. If tails, during your opponent's next turn, they can't play any Item cards from their hand.

name: Paras
flavorText: The mushrooms, known as tochukaso, are controlling the bug. Even if the bug bugs the mushrooms, they tell it to bug off.
Attack1Text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Parasect
flavorText: The bug is mostly dead, with the mushroom on its back having become the main body. If the mushroom comes off, the bug stops moving.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may make both Active Pokemon Asleep and Poisoned.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 50 more damage.

name: Wurmple
flavorText: It lives among the tall grass and in forests. It repels attacks by raising up the spikes on its rear.
Attack2Text: Search your deck for any number of Wurmple, Silcoon, Beautifly, Cascoon, and Dustox, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Silcoon
flavorText: It drinks dew that collects on its silk and waits for evolution. Its hard cocoon repels attacks.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't attack.

name: Beautifly
flavorText: It has an aggressive nature. It stabs prey with its long, narrow mouth to drain the prey's fluids.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Cascoon
flavorText: It never forgets any attack it endured while in the cocoon. After evolution, it seeks payback.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks if that damage is 60 or less.

name: Dustox
flavorText: Tends to be drawn to bonfires on dark nights. Difficult to chase away from settlements because of the way it scatters highly toxic scales.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused and Poisoned. During Pokemon Checkup, put 8 damage counters on that Pokemon instead of 1.

name: Seedot
flavorText: If it remains still, it looks just like a real nut. It delights in surprising foraging Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Nuzleaf
flavorText: It lives deep in forests. With the leaf on its head, it makes a flute whose song makes listeners uneasy.
Attack1Text: You may have your opponent switch their Active Pokemon with 1 of their Benched Pokemon.

name: Shiftry
flavorText: A Pokemon that was feared as a forest guardian. It can read the foe's mind and take preemptive action.
Attack1Text: You may have your opponent switch their Active Pokemon with 1 of their Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Put this Pokemon and all attached cards in the Lost Zone.

name: Roselia
flavorText: Its flowers give off a relaxing fragrance. The stronger its aroma, the healthier the Roselia is.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Roserade
flavorText: After captivating opponents with its sweet scent, it lashes them with its thorny whips.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is affected by a Special Condition, this attack also does 60 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Phantump
flavorText: After a lost child perished in the forest, their spirit possessed a tree stump, causing the spirit's rebirth as this Pokemon.

name: Trevenant
flavorText: People fear it due to a belief that it devours any who try to cut down trees in its forest, but to the Pokemon it shares its woods with, it's kind.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokemon V, your opponent can't take any Prize cards for it.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Blipbug
flavorText: A constant collector of information, this Pokemon is very smart. Very strong is what it isn't.

name: Dottler
flavorText: It barely moves, but it's still alive. Hiding in its shell without food or water seems to have awakened its psychic powers.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Orbeetle
flavorText: It's famous for its high level of intelligence, and the large size of its brain is proof that it also possesses immense psychic power.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may attach up to 3 Energy cards from your opponent's discard pile to your opponent's Pokemon in any way you like.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Slugma
flavorText: Its body is made of magma. If it doesn't keep moving, its body will cool and harden.
Attack1Text: Attach a Fire Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokemon.

name: Magcargo
flavorText: Its body is as hot as lava and is always billowing. Flames will occasionally burst from its shell.
Attack2Text: Put all Energy attached to this Pokemon in the Lost Zone.

name: Torkoal
flavorText: It burns coal inside its shell for energy. It blows out black soot if it is endangered.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Litwick
flavorText: The flame on its head keeps its body slightly warm. This Pokemon takes lost children by the hand to guide them to the spirit world.
Attack1Text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

name: Lampent
flavorText: This Pokemon appears just before someone passes away, so it's feared as an emissary of death.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Chandelure
flavorText: This Pokemon haunts dilapidated mansions. It sways its arms to hypnotize opponents with the ominous dancing of its flames.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may discard the top 3 cards of your opponent's deck.

name: Delphox V
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned and Confused.
Attack2Text: Put 2 Energy attached to this Pokemon in the Lost Zone. This attack also does 120 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Litleo
flavorText: This hot-blooded Pokemon is filled with curiosity. When it gets angry or starts fighting, its short mane gets hot.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Pyroar
flavorText: The temperature of its breath is over 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit, but Pyroar doesn't use it on its prey. This Pokemon prefers to eat raw meat.
Ability1Text: During Pokemon Checkup, put 4 damage counters on your opponent's Burned Pokemon instead of 2.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Poliwag
flavorText: For Poliwag, swimming is easier than walking. The swirl pattern on its belly is actually part of the Pokemon's innards showing through the skin.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokemon.

name: Poliwhirl
flavorText: Staring at the swirl on its belly causes drowsiness. This trait of Poliwhirl's has been used in place of lullabies to get children to go to sleep.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 50 damage for each heads.

name: Politoed
flavorText: At nightfall, these Pokemon appear on the shores of lakes. They announce their territorial claims by letting out cries that sound like shouting.
Attack1Text: If Poliwag is on your Bench, this attack does 60 more damage. If Poliwhirl is on your Bench, this attack does 90 more damage. If Poliwrath is on your Bench, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Seel
flavorText: Thanks to its thick fat, cold seas don't bother it at all, but it gets tired pretty easily in warm waters.

name: Dewgong
flavorText: It sunbathes on the beach after meals. The rise in its body temperature helps its digestion.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Shuffle any amount of Water Energy from your Pokemon into your deck. This attack does 40 damage for each card you shuffled into your deck in this way.

name: Horsea
flavorText: Horsea makes its home in oceans with gentle currents. If this Pokemon is under attack, it spits out pitch-black ink and escapes.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Seadra
flavorText: It's the males that raise the offspring. While Seadra are raising young, the spines on their backs secrete thicker and stronger poison.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon for each Water Energy attached to this Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Kingdra
flavorText: With the arrival of a storm at sea, this Pokemon will show itself on the surface. When a Kingdra and a Dragonite meet, a fierce battle ensues.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may have either player shuffle their hand and put it on the bottom of their deck. If that player put any cards on the bottom of their deck in this way, they draw 4 cards.

name: Luvdisc
flavorText: Luvdisc makes its home in coral reefs in warm seas. It especially likes sleeping in the space between Corsola's branches.
Attack1Text: Each player reveals the top 2 cards of their deck, then draws those cards.

name: Shellos
flavorText: There's speculation that its appearance is determined by what it eats, but the truth remains elusive.

name: Finneon
flavorText: It lures in prey with its shining tail fins. It stays near the surface during the day and moves to the depths when night falls.
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn, you may attach a Water Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokemon that has the Swim Freely attack.

name: Lumineon
flavorText: They traverse the deep waters as if crawling over the seafloor. The fantastic lights of its fins shine like stars in the night sky.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokemon.

name: Snover
flavorText: One is likely to encounter this Pokemon while out in the snow. There are stories of Snover appearing in human settlements but doing no harm—rather, they bond with the children.

name: Abomasnow
flavorText: If it sees any packs of Darumaka going after Snover, it chases them off, swinging its sizable arms like hammers.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Hisuian Basculin
flavorText: Though it differs from other Basculin in several respects, including demeanor—this one is gentle—I have categorized it as a regional form given the vast array of shared qualities.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Hisuian Basculegion
flavorText: Clads itself in the souls of comrades that perished before fulfilling their goals of journeying upstream. No other species throughout all Hisui's rivers is Basculegion's equal.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each basic Energy card in your discard pile. Then, shuffle those cards into your deck.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Ducklett
flavorText: They are better at swimming than flying, and they happily eat their favorite food, peat moss, as they dive underwater.

name: Swanna
flavorText: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Kyurem V
Attack1Text: Attach any number of Water Energy cards from your hand to your Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Kyurem VMAX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may discard the top card of your deck. If that card is a Water Energy card, attach it to 1 of your Pokemon.
Attack1Text: You may discard any amount of Water Energy from this Pokemon. This attack does 50 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Cramorant
flavorText: It's so strong that it can knock out some opponents in a single hit, but it also may forget what it's battling midfight.
Ability1Text: If you have 4 or more cards in the Lost Zone, ignore all Energy in this Pokemon's attack costs.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness.

name: Glastrier
flavorText: Glastrier emits intense cold from its hooves. It's also a belligerent Pokemon—anything it wants, it takes by force.
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokemon is a Basic Pokemon, it can't attack during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Pikachu
flavorText: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon has any Energy attached, it has no Retreat Cost.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Raichu
flavorText: Its long tail serves as a ground to protect itself from its own high-voltage power.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: If you have used your VSTAR Power, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Electrike
flavorText: It stores static electricity in its fur for discharging. It gives off sparks if a storm approaches.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Manectric
flavorText: It stimulates its own muscles with electricity, so it can move quickly. It eases its soreness with electricity, too, so it can recover quickly as well.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon has a Pokemon Tool attached, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Magnezone V
Attack1Text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon with their Active Pokemon. This attack does 40 damage to the new Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack also does 30 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Magnezone VSTAR
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Item cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: This attack does 90 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.) (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Rotom V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may draw 3 cards. If you use this Ability, your turn ends.
Attack1Text: Put any number of Pokemon Tool cards from your discard pile in the Lost Zone. This attack does 40 more damage for each card you put in the Lost Zone in this way.

name: Tynamo
flavorText: One alone can emit only a trickle of electricity, so a group of them gathers to unleash a powerful electric shock.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Lightning Pokemon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Eelektrik
flavorText: These Pokemon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Eelektross
flavorText: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon's attacks do 120 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokemon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Clefairy
flavorText: It can be found in quiet mountain areas on a full moon's night. Its dancing and its tiny, faintly glowing wings confer upon it a lovely fairylike quality.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, for each of your Benched Clefairy, you may search your deck for a Psychic Energy card and attach it to that Clefairy. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each Psychic Energy attached to all of your Pokemon.

name: Clefable
flavorText: A timid fairy Pokemon that is rarely seen, it will run and hide the moment it senses people.
Ability1Text: All of your Pokemon take 30 less damage from attacks from your opponent's Dragon Pokemon (after applying Weakness and Resistance). You can't apply more than 1 Spirit Charm Ability at a time.

name: Gastly
flavorText: Born from gases, anyone would faint if engulfed by its gaseous body, which contains poison.
Attack1Text: Put 1 damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Haunter
flavorText: This frightful, malevolent spirit can glide through walls, appearing wherever it likes. According to rumor, victims of a Haunter's lick will wither to death day by day.
Attack1Text: Put 3 damage counters on your opponent's Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Gengar
flavorText: On the night of a full moon, if shadows move on their own and laugh, it must be Gengar's doing.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokemon is in your discard pile, you may put it onto your Bench. If you do, put 3 damage counters on this Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Put 2 damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokemon for each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon.

name: Mr. Mime
flavorText: The behavior of this clown-like Pokemon reminds one of pantomime. It creates invisible walls using a force emitted from its fingertips.
Attack2Text: You and your opponent play Rock-Paper-Scissors until someone wins. If you win, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokemon.

name: Jynx
flavorText: Its strange cries sound like human language. There are some musicians who compose songs for Jynx to sing.
Attack1Text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon with their Active Pokemon. The new Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Radiant Gardevoir
flavorText: It has the power to predict the future. Its power peaks when it is protecting its Trainer.
Ability1Text: All of your Pokemon take 20 less damage from attacks from your opponent's Pokemon V (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Sableye
flavorText: This Pokemon is feared. When its gemstone eyes begin to glow with a sinister shine, it's believed that Sableye will steal people's spirits away.
Attack2Text: You can use this attack only if you have 10 or more cards in the Lost Zone. Put 12 damage counters on your opponent's Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Mawile
flavorText: It uses its docile-looking face to lull foes into complacency, then bites with its huge, relentless jaws.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat. During your next turn, the Defending Pokemon takes 90 more damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Shuppet
flavorText: There's a proverb that says, "Shun the house where Shuppet gather in the growing dusk."

name: Banette
flavorText: Resentment at being cast off made it spring into being. Some say that treating it well will satisfy it, and it will once more become a stuffed toy.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may put a Supporter card from your discard pile into your hand. If you do, put this Pokemon in the Lost Zone. (Discard all attached cards.)

name: Cresselia
flavorText: Those who sleep holding Cresselia's feather are assured of joyful dreams. It is said to represent the crescent moon.
Attack1Text: Move 2 damage counters from each of your Pokemon to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon.

name: Hisuian Zorua
flavorText: A once-departed soul, returned to life in Hisui. Derives power from resentment, which rises as energy atop its head and takes on the forms of foes. In this way, Zorua vents lingering malice.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.

name: Hisuian Zoroark
flavorText: With its disheveled white fur, it looks like an embodiment of death. Heedless of its own safety, Zoroark attacks its nemeses with a bitter energy so intense, it lacerates Zoroark's own body.
Attack1Text: At the end of your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon will be Knocked Out.
Attack2Text: Put a card from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Inkay
flavorText: It spins while making its luminescent spots flash. These spots allow it to communicate with others by using different patterns of light.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Malamar
flavorText: Gazing at its luminescent spots will quickly induce a hypnotic state, putting the observer under Malamar's control.
Attack1Text: Each player reveals their hand. If a card in your opponent's hand has the same name as a card in your hand, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Comfey
flavorText: Comfey picks flowers with its vine and decorates itself with them. For some reason, flowers won't wither once they're attached to a Comfey.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, you may look at the top 2 cards of your deck and put 1 of them into your hand. Put the other card in the Lost Zone.

name: Mimikyu
flavorText: It wears a rag fashioned into a Pikachu costume in an effort to look less scary. Unfortunately, the costume only makes it creepier.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: This attack does 10 damage for each damage counter on all of your opponent's Pokemon.

name: Spectrier
flavorText: It probes its surroundings with all its senses save one—it doesn't use its sense of sight. Spectrier's kicks are said to separate soul from body.
Attack1Text: Choose 2 of your opponent's Pokemon and put 2 damage counters on each of them.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't use Phantom Strike.

name: Enamorus V
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of your opponent's Pokemon's Abilities done to each of your Pokemon that has any Psychic Energy attached, except any Enamorus V.
Attack1Text: Attach up to 2 basic Energy cards from your discard pile to your Benched Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Hisuian Growlithe
flavorText: They patrol their territory in pairs. I believe the igneous rock components in the fur of this species are the result of volcanic activity in its habitat.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Hisuian Arcanine
flavorText: Snaps at its foes with fangs cloaked in blazing flame. Despite its bulk, it deftly feints every which way, leading opponents on a deceptively merry chase as it all but dances around them.
Attack1Text: If you have no cards in your hand, this attack does 150 more damage.

name: Poliwrath
flavorText: Its body is solid muscle. When swimming through cold seas, Poliwrath uses its impressive arms to smash through drift ice and plow forward.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: Put 2 Energy attached to this Pokemon into your hand.

name: Machop
flavorText: Its whole body is composed of muscles. Even though it's the size of a human child, it can hurl 100 grown-ups.

name: Machoke
flavorText: A sturdy creature boasting a robust physique and boundless stamina. Loves training above all else and voluntarily assists with tasks such as construction and clearing land.

name: Machamp
flavorText: It quickly swings its four arms to rock its opponents with ceaseless punches and chops from all angles.
Ability1Text: If your opponent has 3 or fewer Prize cards remaining, this Pokemon gets +150 HP.
Attack1Text: You may do 100 more damage. If you do, during your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Rhyhorn
flavorText: Strong, but not too bright, this Pokemon can shatter even a skyscraper with its charging tackles.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 20 damage to itself.

name: Rhydon
flavorText: It begins walking on its hind legs after evolution. It can punch holes through boulders with its horn.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Rhyperior
flavorText: It can load up to three projectiles per arm into the holes in its hands. What launches out of those holes could be either rocks or Roggenrola.
Attack1Text: Discard the top card of your deck. If that card is an Energy card, this attack does 100 more damage, and attach that card to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Aerodactyl V
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Aerodactyl VSTAR
Attack1Text: Put the top 3 cards of your deck in the Lost Zone.
Attack2Text: Until this Pokemon leaves play, it gains an Ability that has the effect "Your opponent's Pokemon V in play, except any Aerodactyl VSTAR, have no Abilities." (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Sudowoodo
flavorText: Though it pretends to be a tree, it fails to fool even children. To the touch, its body feels more like rock than tree bark. Sudowoodo's extreme aversion to water merits special note.
Attack1Text: Before doing damage, discard all Pokemon Tools from your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.

name: Gligar
flavorText: It flies straight at its target's face, then clamps down on the startled victim to inject poison.
Attack1Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Gliscor
flavorText: Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to carry off its prey... Then its elongated fangs do the rest.
Attack1Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 50 damage for each heads. If at least 2 of them are heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Makuhita
flavorText: There's a rumor of a traditional recipe for stew that Trainers can use to raise strong Makuhita.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Hariyama
flavorText: Hariyama that are big and fat aren't necessarily strong. There are some small ones that move nimbly and use moves skillfully.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

name: Meditite
flavorText: It eats just one berry a day. By enduring hunger, its spirit is tempered and made sharper.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Medicham
flavorText: Through yoga training, it gained the psychic power to predict its foe's next move.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Fighting Energy cards and attach them to your Benched Pokemon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Relicanth
flavorText: Rock-hard scales and oil-filled swim bladders allow this Pokemon to survive the intense water pressure of the deep sea.
Attack1Text: Put up to 2 basic Energy cards from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Gastrodon
flavorText: Its search for food sometimes leads it onto land, where it leaves behind a sticky trail of slime as it passes through.
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon and heal all damage from it.
Attack2Text: This attack also does 20 damage to each of your Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Mienfoo
flavorText: In one minute, a well-trained Mienfoo can chop with its arms more than 100 times.

name: Mienshao
flavorText: When Mienshao comes across a truly challenging opponent, it will lighten itself by biting off the fur on its arms.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 70 damage for each heads.

name: Landorus
flavorText: From the forces of lightning and wind, it creates energy to give nutrients to the soil and make the land abundant.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Binacle
flavorText: After two Binacle find a suitably sized rock, they adhere themselves to it and live together. They cooperate to gather food during high tide.

name: Barbaracle
flavorText: Seven Binacle come together to form one Barbaracle. The Binacle that serves as the head gives orders to those serving as the limbs.
Ability1Text: Your opponent puts any Prize cards they would take in the Lost Zone instead of into their hand.

name: Carbink
flavorText: When beset by attackers, Carbink wipes them all out by firing high-energy beams from the gems embedded in its body.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Item cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Rockruff
flavorText: This Pokemon can bond very strongly with its Trainer, but it also has a habit of biting. Raising a Rockruff for a long time can be challenging.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.

name: Falinks
flavorText: Five of them are troopers, and one is the brass. The brass's orders are absolute.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness. If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Pokemon V, this attack does 50 more damage.

name: Stonjourner
flavorText: It stands in grasslands, watching the sun's descent from zenith to horizon. This Pokemon has a talent for delivering dynamic kicks.
Attack1Text: Attach up to 2 Fighting Energy cards from your hand to your Pokemon in any way you like.
Attack2Text: Put the top card of your opponent's deck in the Lost Zone.

name: Spinarak
flavorText: Although the poison from its fangs isn't that strong, it's potent enough to weaken prey that gets caught in its web.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Ariados
flavorText: It spews threads from its mouth to catch its prey. When night falls, it leaves its web to go hunt aggressively.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokemon's Retreat Cost.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Murkrow
flavorText: It searches for shiny things for its boss. Murkrow's presence is said to be unlucky, so many people detest it.

name: Honchkrow
flavorText: Its goons take care of most of the fighting for it. The only time it dirties its own hands is in delivering a final blow to finish off an opponent.
Attack2Text: Move all Energy from this Pokemon to your Benched Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Seviper
flavorText: Constant polishing makes the edge of the blade on its tail extremely sharp. It's Zangoose's archrival.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Darkness Pokemon.

name: Spiritomb
flavorText: Exactly 108 spirits gathered to become this Pokemon. Apparently there are some ill-natured spirits in the mix.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokemon, search your deck for a card and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: This attack does 60 more damage for each Spiritomb in your discard pile.

name: Drapion V
Ability1Text: This Pokemon's attacks cost Colorless less for each of your opponent's Single Strike, Rapid Strike, and Fusion Strike Pokemon in play.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 60 damage to 1 of your Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Drapion VSTAR
Ability1Text: During your turn, you may make your opponent's Active Pokemon Paralyzed and Poisoned. During Pokemon Checkup, put 3 damage counters on that Pokemon instead of 1. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 less damage for each damage counter on this Pokemon.

name: Darkrai
flavorText: On a moonless night, a strange incident occurred in which every one of a village's inhabitants suffered nightmares. The villagers attested that Darkrai appeared before them in these nightmares.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Inkay
flavorText: It spins while making its luminescent spots flash. These spots allow it to communicate with others by using different patterns of light.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokemon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Hoopa
flavorText: It gathers things it likes and passes them through its loop to teleport them to a secret place.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Darkness Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Radiant Hisuian Sneasler
flavorText: Because of Sneasler's virulent poison and daunting physical prowess, no other species could hope to best it on the frozen highlands. Preferring solitude, this species does not form packs.
Ability1Text: During Pokemon Checkup, put 2 more damage counters on your opponent's Poisoned Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Radiant Steelix
flavorText: It is said that if an Onix lives for over 100 years, its composition changes to become diamond-like.
Attack1Text: Attach up to 2 Metal Energy cards from your discard pile to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Discard cards from the top of your deck until only 1 card remains. This attack does 30 more damage for each Energy card you discarded in this way.

name: Bronzor
flavorText: It appears in ancient ruins. The pattern on its body doesn't come from any culture in the Galar region, so it remains shrouded in mystery.

name: Bronzong
flavorText: Some believe that its bell-like cry opens holes to another world. It has been revered as a deity since ancient times.
Attack2Text: This attack does 40 more damage for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokemon's Retreat Cost.

name: Galarian Stunfisk
flavorText: Living in mud with a high iron content has given it a strong steel body.
Attack1Text: If your opponent has a Stadium in play, discard it. If you discarded a Stadium in this way, discard 2 Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Magearna
flavorText: Built roughly 500 years ago by a scientist, the part called the Soul-Heart is the actual life-form.
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon has a Pokemon Tool attached, this attack does 60 more damage, and your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Galarian Perrserker V
Attack1Text: Draw 3 cards.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 damage for each card in your hand.

name: Giratina V
Attack1Text: Look at the top 4 cards of your deck and put 2 of them into your hand. Put the other cards in the Lost Zone.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Giratina VSTAR
Attack1Text: Put 2 Energy attached to your Pokemon in the Lost Zone.
Attack2Text: You can use this attack only if you have 10 or more cards in the Lost Zone. Your opponent's Active Pokemon is Knocked Out. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Goomy
flavorText: Goomy hides away in the shade of trees, where it's nice and humid. If the slime coating its body dries out, the Pokemon instantly becomes lethargic.

name: Hisuian Sliggoo
flavorText: A creature given to melancholy. I suspect its metallic shell developed as a result of the mucus on its skin reacting with the iron in Hisui's water.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 50 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Hisuian Goodra
flavorText: Able to freely control the hardness of its metallic shell. It loathes solitude and is extremely clingy—it will fume and run riot if those dearest to it ever leave its side.
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to each of your Basic Pokemon that has any Metal Energy attached by attacks from your opponent's Pokemon V.

name: Hisuian Goodra V
Attack1Text: Your opponent switches their Active Pokemon with 1 of their Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Hisuian Goodra VSTAR
Ability1Text: During your turn, you may heal all damage from this Pokemon. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 80 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Pidgeot V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokemon is on your Bench, you may shuffle it and all attached cards into your deck.
Attack1Text: If you have a Stadium in play, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Lickitung
flavorText: If this Pokemon's sticky saliva gets on you and you don't clean it off, an intense itch will set in. The itch won't go away, either.

name: Lickilicky
flavorText: Lickilicky's strange tongue can stretch to many times the length of its body. No one has figured out how Lickilicky's tongue can stretch so far.

name: Porygon
flavorText: State-of-the-art technology was used to create Porygon. It was the first artificial Pokemon to be created via computer programming.
Attack1Text: Look at the top 4 cards of either player's deck and put them back in any order.

name: Porygon2
flavorText: This is a Porygon that was updated with special data. Porygon2 develops itself by learning about many different subjects all on its own.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each Pokemon Tool card in the Lost Zone (both yours and your opponent's).

name: Porygon-Z
flavorText: Porygon-Z had a program installed to allow it to move between dimensions, but the program also caused instability in Porygon-Z's behavior.
Attack1Text: Devolve 1 of your opponent's evolved Pokemon by removing any number of Evolution cards from it. Your opponent shuffles those cards into their deck.

name: Snorlax
flavorText: It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of attacks from your opponent's Pokemon done to this Pokemon. (Damage is not an effect.)
Attack1Text: This Pokemon is now Asleep. During Pokemon Checkup, flip 2 coins instead of 1. If either of them is tails, this Pokemon is still Asleep.

name: Aipom
flavorText: This treetop dweller possesses a tail as dexterous as a hand. Ancient writings describe this Pokemon as a one-armed oddity.
Attack1Text: Look at the top card of your opponent's deck. You may have your opponent shuffle their deck.

name: Ambipom
flavorText: It uses its tails for everything. If it wraps both of its tails around you and gives you a squeeze, that's proof it really likes you.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. Search your deck for a number of cards up to the number of heads and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

name: Hisuian Zoroark V
Attack1Text: You may switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Move an Energy from this Pokemon to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Hisuian Zoroark VSTAR
Ability1Text: During your turn, you may discard your hand and draw 7 cards. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage for each of your Pokemon that has any damage counters on it.

name: Bouffalant
flavorText: These Pokemon can crush a car with no more than a headbutt. Bouffalant with more hair on their heads hold higher positions within the herd.
Attack1Text: Put an Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon in the Lost Zone.

name: Komala
flavorText: It remains asleep from birth to death as a result of the sedative properties of the leaves that form its diet.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is Asleep and is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokemon, your opponent can't take any Prize cards for it.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Skwovet
flavorText: Found throughout the Galar region, this Pokemon becomes uneasy if its cheeks are ever completely empty of berries.

name: Greedent
flavorText: It stashes berries in its tail—so many berries that they fall out constantly. But this Pokemon is a bit slow-witted, so it doesn't notice the loss.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.
Attack2Text: Discard your hand. If you discarded 5 or more cards in this way, this attack does 150 more damage.

name: Hisuian Electrode V
Attack1Text: This attack does 100 damage for each Special Condition affecting this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Discard all Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Delphox V
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned and Confused.
Attack2Text: Put 2 Energy attached to this Pokemon in the Lost Zone. This attack also does 120 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Kyurem V
Attack1Text: Attach any number of Water Energy cards from your hand to your Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Magnezone V
Attack1Text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon with their Active Pokemon. This attack does 40 damage to the new Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack also does 30 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Rotom V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may draw 3 cards. If you use this Ability, your turn ends.
Attack1Text: Put any number of Pokemon Tool cards from your discard pile in the Lost Zone. This attack does 40 more damage for each card you put in the Lost Zone in this way.

name: Rotom V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may draw 3 cards. If you use this Ability, your turn ends.
Attack1Text: Put any number of Pokemon Tool cards from your discard pile in the Lost Zone. This attack does 40 more damage for each card you put in the Lost Zone in this way.

name: Enamorus V
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of your opponent's Pokemon's Abilities done to each of your Pokemon that has any Psychic Energy attached, except any Enamorus V.
Attack1Text: Attach up to 2 basic Energy cards from your discard pile to your Benched Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Aerodactyl V
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Aerodactyl V
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Gallade V
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Prize card you have taken.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may discard the top card of your deck. If that card is a Water Energy card, attach it to 1 of your Pokemon.
Attack1Text: You may discard any amount of Water Energy from this Pokemon. This attack does 50 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Magnezone VSTAR
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Item cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: This attack does 90 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.) (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Aerodactyl VSTAR
Attack1Text: Put the top 3 cards of your deck in the Lost Zone.
